This was the first centerfire rifle used by the US military and was the rifle that Custer's men were armed with at the Battle of Little Bighorn.  Chambered in 45-70, this rifle is ready for the range.  Bore still shows good rifling.  Ammo is still widely available.  This gun still has most of its original bluing.  It has never been scrubbed or sanded in any way and still retains that perfect patina.  The cartouche is still visible and under a magnifying glass it reads 1882.  The circle P cartouche is visible and legible under the wrist.

This rifle has an amazing history to it.  It was owned by a famous civil war vet.  Obviously this is not a civil war rifle, but it was used on the American frontier.  I can fill you in on the history of it.  I received this rifle from the great grandson of the civil war vet that owned this rifle.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield Model 1873 Trapdoor- 45-70- All Original
postcontent:
This is an all original Springfield Model 1873 Trapdoor rifle.  This was the first centerfire rifle used by the US military and was the rifle that Custer's men were armed with at the Battle of Little Bighorn.  Chambered in 45-70, this rifle is ready for the range.  Bore still shows good rifling.  Ammo is still widely available.  This gun still has most of its original bluing.  It has never been scrubbed or sanded in any way and still retains that perfect patina.  The cartouche is still visible and under a magnifying glass it reads 1882.  The circle P cartouche is visible and legible under the wrist.  

This rifle has an amazing history to it.  It was owned by a famous civil war vet.  Obviously this is not a civil war rifle, but it was used on the American frontier.  I can fill you in on the history of it.  I received this rifle from the great grandson of the civil war vet that owned this rifle.
